  "prompt": "What are some best songs to listen to?",
  "response": "The best songs to listen to can vary greatly depending on personal taste, mood, and the occasion. However, here are some popular and timeless songs across various genres that many people enjoy:\n\n### Pop\n1. **\"Blinding Lights\" - The Weeknd**\n2. **\"Levitating\" - Dua Lipa (feat. DaBaby)**\n3. **\"Watermelon Sugar\" - Harry Styles**\n\n### Rock\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" - Queen**\n2. **\"Hotel California\" - Eagles**\n3. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" - Led Zeppelin**\n\n### Hip-Hop/Rap\n1. **\"Sicko Mode\" - Travis Scott**\n2. **\"God's Plan\" - Drake**\n3. **\"HUMBLE.\" - Kendrick Lamar**\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **\"Adorn\" - Miguel**\n2. **\"Leave The Door Open\" - Silk Sonic**\n3. **\"Slow Dancing in the Dark\" - Joji**\n\n### Indie/Alternative\n1. **\"Take Me Out\" - Franz Ferdinand**\n2. **\"Dog Days Are Over\" - Florence + The Machine**\n3. **\"Electric Feel\" - MGMT**\n\n### Classics\n1. **\"Imagine\" - John Lennon**\n2. **\"I Want to Hold Your Hand\" - The Beatles**\n3. **\"What\u2019s Going On\" - Marvin Gaye**\n\n### Chill/Relaxing\n1. **\"Come Away With Me\" - Norah Jones**\n2. **\"River\" - Leon Bridges**\n3. **\"Put It All On Me\" - Ed Sheeran**\n\n### Uplifting/Feel-Good\n1. **\"Happy\" - Pharrell Williams**\n2. **\"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" - Justin Timberlake**\n3. **\"Uptown Funk\" - Mark Ronson (feat. Bruno Mars)**\n\n### Playlist Suggestions\n- **Workout Playlist:** Songs with high energy like \"Eye of the Tiger\" - Survivor, and \"Stronger\" - Kanye West.\n- **Relaxing Playlist:** Soft tunes like \"Holocene\" - Bon Iver, and \"Budapest\" - George Ezra.\n- **Party Playlist:** Upbeat tracks like \"Party in the USA\" - Miley Cyrus, and \"Shake It Off\" - Taylor Swift.\n\nFeel free to explore these songs and see what resonates with you!",
